Here's a question about the word 'inane:'  (I'm not going to look it up, I enjoy speculating)<br>
<br>
Inane is an adjective, much like how insane is an adjective.  Insane describes someone or something possessing the quality of insanity (a noun).  So...is there a noun form of inane?  'Inanity' just sounds funny, and I'm not about to be content with 'inaneness.'  Any thoughts?  If you look it up, you're cheating.  :] <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=205399"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://mywebpages.comcast.net/vicour1/NandSig.gif" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
